This paper discusses the use of machine learning in addressing demographic disparities in various domains such as employment, credit, and healthcare. It focuses on the availability of sensitive attribute data for antidiscrimination purposes and the legal and corporate practices surrounding their collection and inference. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CS (Computational Complexity).
